#Text=Raleigh
#Text=The capital of North Carolina and the largest city of the Research Triangle , Raleigh is the primary political and economic driver of the metro area .
#Text=Indeed , business and politics are the main draws to Raleigh , which lacks the more trendy feel or active arts scene of Durham or Chapel Hill to the west .
#Text=However , a concerted effort to expand the residential base and move events downtown has led to significantly expanded retail and restaurant options in the downtown core .

#Text=Also , visitors will find many of the state 's cultural institutions here , namely a major performing arts center downtown and three state museums , and a college town atmosphere in the neighborhood around the campus of North Carolina State University , the state 's largest university .
#Text=History
#Text=Raleigh is one of the few U.S. state capitals that was specifically established and planned to serve as a capital .

#Text=Its location was chosen partly for being near the center of the state and partly because it was close to Isaac Hunter 's Tavern , where North Carolina legislators and other government officials liked to stay .

#Text=The story goes that the commissioners could n't decide on an exact plot of land until Isaac Hunter and his friend Joel Lane had the idea of throwing a big party with plenty of local jam and whiskey .
#Text=The next morning , the hungover commissioners voted 5 – 1 for a plot owned by Joel Lane himself .
#Text=The new city was officially established as the state capital in 1792 and was named for Sir Walter Raleigh .
#Text=Visitor information
#Text=The Greater Raleigh Convention and Visitors Bureau operates the Raleigh Visitor Information Center .
#Text=The Visitor Information Center ( VIC ) is located at 500 Fayetteville Street between the Raleigh Marriott City Center and The Raleigh Convention Center .
#Text=The VIC is open Monday thru Saturday , 9AM to 5PM and offers brochures , event calendars , coupons , maps , and other visitor information .
#Text=Stop by and pick up a brochure or visit the website to view a visitor guide online or order one to be mailed before your trip .
#Text=By plane
#Text=Raleigh-Durham International Airport ( RDU ) .
#Text=A former hub of American Airlines and Midway Airlines , the airport today is a fairly large focus city for Delta Airlines .
#Text=The airport has bus service in the form of GoTriangle Route 100 , which stops at the airport on the way from the Regional Transit Center to downtown Raleigh .
#Text=By car
#Text=Interstate 40 goes to points west including Durham , Chapel Hill , Greensboro , Winston-Salem , and Asheville .
#Text=Two and a half hours east on I-40 is Wilmington .

#Text=Interstates 85 and 95 , though they do not directly enter Raleigh , provide easy access to the city from up and down the Eastern Seaboard ; large access routes from these interstates provide easy access to the city .
#Text=US 1 , the East Coast corridor route , cuts through Raleigh on its way from New York to the Florida Keys ; within the city limits US 1 is known as Capital Blvd.
#Text=By train
#Text=Amtrak provides train services to Raleigh ; the Piedmont runs three times per day from Charlotte , a trip of just over three hours .
#Text=There are also two daily long-distance routes : the Carolinian and Silver Star lines , both of which head north through Richmond , Washington , D.C. and Philadelphia to New York City .
#Text=Southbound , the Carolinian follows the Piedmont south to Charlotte and the Silver Star heads south through Columbia and Savannah to Florida .
#Text=The new , at 510 W Martin St , has completely replaced the old station .
#Text=By bus
#Text=Greyhound , 2210 Capital Blvd , +1 919 834-8275 .
#Text=Megabus stops in nearby Durham .
#Text=Triangle Transit , +1 919 549-9999 .
#Text=The Triangle 's inter-city bus service runs routes between Raleigh , Durham , Chapel Hill and RDU , with a hub near the Research Triangle Park .
#Text=Fares are $ 2.25 per trip and $ 4.50 for a day pass .
#Text=Get around
#Text=Within the I-440 Beltline are mostly fashionable older neighborhoods and the NC State University area .

#Text=The North Raleigh neighborhoods are aligned along the " spokes of the wheel " — major thoroughfares emanating from the I-440 Loop and passing through the northern edge of the much larger I-540 loop .
#Text=Downtown Raleigh provides easy travel and access through its grid of one-way streets .
#Text=If you 're just passing through , the major thoroughfare is Capital Boulevard ( US 401 ) , which splits into Dawson Street heading south and McDowell Street heading north .
#Text=From the west , it is Hillsborough Street , interrupted midway by the state Capitol building .
#Text=To the east , it continues as New Bern Avenue ( US 64 ) .
#Text=The I-440 Beltline was once denoted with " Inner " and " Outer " labels , but they have been phased out in favor of " East " and " West .

column1: #Text=By bus
#Text=For information on routes , schedules and fares , check GoTriangle.org , for a helpful trip planner .
#Text=Triangle Transit Authority ( TTA ) , +1 919 549-9999 .
#Text=Routes between Raleigh , Durham , Cary , and Chapel Hill as well as Research Triangle Park and the Raleigh-Durham International Airport .
#Text=Capital Area Transit ( CAT ) , +1 919 828-7228 .
#Text=Routes within Raleigh city limits including a free downtown circulator bus , the R-Line .
#Text=Wolfline , +1 919 515-9653 .
#Text=Routes in and around NC State University ; free and open to the public .
#Text=Note that Triangle Transit passes ( $ 4.50 for a 1-day pass ) can also be used on CAT and buses in Durham and Cary .
#Text=But the reverse is not true ; CAT passes ( $ 2 for 1-day ) are only usable on CAT .
